<h3 style="margin-top:1.5em">How To Run the Program From PowerShell (Windows):</h3>

<ol>
<li>https://www.python.org/downloads/ Install Python version 3.10</li>
<li>In start menu, type powershell.</li>
<li>Open Powershell.</li>
<li><dl><dt>Install the required modules using the pip install cmdlets: </dt>
	<dd> - pip install flask</dd>
	<dd> - pip install pandas</li>
	<dd> - pip install vaderSentiment</dd>
	<dd> - pip install requests</dd></dl> 
	</li>
<li>Download the program files from Github.</li>
<li>Place the folder containing GRSA 1.0 files where you want it to stay.</li>
<li>Select the app.py file in the GRSA 1.0 folder. Right-click and open "properties".</li>
<li>Copy the "Location" field from this file.</li>
<li>In Powershell type "Python /app.py"</li>
<li>Hit Enter to run the program.</li>
<li>In your browser type "localhost:5001" to access the User Interface.</li>
<li>Copy/paste the URL from the game you're intersted in from the Valve store website into the URL field of the GRSA user interface.</li>
<li>Click Submit</li>
</ol>


